               <img alt="" class="wide-image" data-attrs='{"src":"https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/537fa2ce-915a-45b0-9218-5a4467fd0a88_751x623.png","height":623,"width":751,"resizeWidth":602,"bytes":null,"alt":null,"title":null,"type":null,"href":null}' src="https://cdn.substack.com/image/fetch/w_1204,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F537fa2ce-915a-45b0-9218-5a4467fd0a88_751x623.png" style="-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic; border: none !important; display: block; height: auto; margin: 0 auto; margin-bottom: 0; max-width: 550px; vertical-align: middle; width: 100%;" width="550"/>
              </a>
             </td>
             <td style="text-align: center;">
             </td>
            </tr>
           </tbody>
          </table>
         </figure>
        </div>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         We need tools for the next era of social networks, creators, and businesses to engage with their community while monetizing along the way. The time is right.
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Cultural tailwinds
           </strong>
           support inclusive economic models as opposed to the extractive models that defined the first decade of the gig economy.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkN2OhCAMhZ9muNMIgjoXXMzNvobhpyoRwUDZiW-_zEyym03aNOlJe9rPKIQ1pkueMSMpGdLsrKQDm3rB78RKbukkJuLyvCSAQzkvMRUgZ9HeGYUuhvdE1zFBNsm1Gew0CNtbZg3whfIFtGATH_XIRk1ePrMq1kEwIOEb0hUDEC83xDPf-seNfdUIEXVMLqxtLjqjMntr4lGFs2aOCz5VgsblBuoJYW1wg-ZQaQfMxEnWsY5Seqe96Luxpa3KfgRW2Bn2G--Olf1bS5L89avyvqkD_FuoX861HiU4vGYISnuwHwD4Qfb-B68TZIBn9oAI6dN8UZnGYRBckOpmY4UX_ox-AOIugyI" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
             Software is eating the markets
            </a>
           </strong>
           , giving more people knowledge of, comfort with, and access to, new investment opportunities.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Crypto
           </strong>
           is making it possible to
           <strong>
            financialize everything
           </strong>
           .
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Bitcoin is ripping, up 57% over the past month heading into Thanksgiving. It\xe2\x80\x99s eerily reminiscent of the 2017 Crypto Bubble, but it\xe2\x80\x99s different this time. With use cases becoming clearer, Crypto 2020 is much more about the infrastructure on top of which a wave of killer apps are being built.
        </p>
        <h3 style="color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Compact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;">
         <strong>
          Web3 and Crypto
         </strong>
        </h3>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          If we assume that the WWW has revolutionized information and the Web2 revolutionizes interactions, the Web3 has the potential to revolutionize agreements and value exchange. It changes the data structures in the backend of the Internet, introducing a universal state layer, by incentivizing network actors with a token.
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         <em>
          -- Shermin Voshmgir,
          <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxNUbGO3CAU_BrTxYKHbXBBcUq00jXXXFJbGJ69aDFYgG-1-fqw3iInIWDmzWOAMbrgGtND7TEXcmRMk7OKDSB5343Eqs4y2Uvi8rQkxE07r0o6kOzH7J3RxcVwdlAKPbkqKpdxRrp0yDXjbFn02MleLNaKeTZzR54-kz6sw2BQ4RemRwxIvLqWsueGvzVwqeN-v7d6039jaC1WvO512lO0hyl1x0cJjHIJooKES8N_6Tx5NxXf8IvDiv_8vsgGhqLXCvIV0-aCRcr0D2CVN3rba4EN_KkyCetTvp59g-igMt6F289o8TwZvknePt8_Kvn9Bqf43Va2Ez3nAyw9wKAlSJhBMouDQCMpFYI4BRQoY2xkvOdUtKzV2QuEA_Zwazq6rdDmY85Fm1tr4kaSCrHMMbmw1vLtqjf0Z6EmMNV1O4IrjwmDnj3aVzjlFef51-Wxowp4zx5LwfQin4lJMQx915PqZmMNNvw3-gdfwKvb" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
           Token Economy
          </a>
         </em>
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         \xe2\x80\x9cCrypto\xe2\x80\x9d comes with a lot of baggage, so it might help to boil it down to the three main use cases in the context of the
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkM2OwyAMhJ-m3BIBCfk5cNjLvkZEwGlQE4PAtMrbL20PK1myPKPRyJ81BPeQLh1DJlYypMU7LQY5daqfmdO9E5OamM_LlgBO4w9NqQCLZT28NeQDfhKcS8V27Zxb537oxCqE5dvMN8nHTsyzsfM0KsXePYspzgNa0PCEdAUEduidKOZb93OTv3WeJnmD1G4FXT1phya8EFLefWzABgzn1dh0RQqNQddUJZcTUpPDRi-ToIaY15JLLoSYRac6PraiNfkYQRYZ8XHr-XmXbS5rJmMfrQ0nSxoDrSF5vFf7sZsTjo9R313qPgt6uhZAsx7gviToy-7zGF0RNMIrH0AE6Su-8UzjMKhesdrmQqWI_0V_I_yGGg" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Ownership Economy
         </a>
         :
        </p>
        <ol style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Financial.
           </strong>
           Raise funding that communities, creators, and companies need to create things while aligning your upside with early fans, workers, and other participants.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Social.
           </strong>
           Create a community around you in which your fans and users engage and become your distribution. There\xe2\x80\x99s also an element of social signaling that you were the first involved, and tiered access to exclusive rewards.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            Governance.
           </strong>
           Give stakeholders a voice in the decisions about your business, platform, or community.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ol>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         It is still incredibly early. Instead of thinking of crypto as a full-fledged product, think of it as a new set of tools engineers and entrepreneurs can use to build. Just as the internet in the late \xe2\x80\x9890s was engineering-heavy and design-light, crypto thus far has focused too much on the technology and not enough on the user experience, too much on what is technically possible and not enough on how it can improve people\xe2\x80\x99s lives.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         There is a vibrant ecosystem of new projects that are powering the infrastructure for social tokens, including:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOwyAM_JpyjIIJeRw47GV_IyLgtmwJIDAb5e-XtIeVLFua0Wg8YzThI-ZTpViI1YJ5dVbxEWYhh4VZNVg-y5m5st4z4q6dV5QrslQ374wmF8Nb0fcg2VON02JAiFELMMssYdju3OCmrZCwCJjZ5bPqah0Ggwp_MZ8xIPPqSZTKTXzd4LvNcRxdyjGVtn7QUGfi3mDmFPTQc84XLqTop453uvgJoUIKr9vQ7w_oSt0KafO6RCyrEGmL2YVHo19PvaN_Ey3B2u5eg6NzxaA3j_YTjj51vH-lM6EKeBSPRJg_4JV4nsZRDpI1NxtbMeHf6A8ryXUD" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
             Props Project
            </a>
           </strong>
           is a turbocharged loyalty program that rewards people with tokens for doing things like sharing and engaging.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUEmOhSAQPY0sjYDjgkVv-hqGoVQiAoGiO96--bropJJK3kvVG7RE2EO6RQwZScmQVmsEHdnMh34hRvSGzsNMbF63BHBJ6wSmAiQW5ayWaIN_LrqODeQQhkm1cT2C0lTyedH9ordNLqPpuWKUkY_OKoux4DUI-IF0Bw_EiQMx5oZ_Ney7zhaKN8_3VsZYAWIF61hHKV0oH3g3tbSV2U3ACov-bPru2lmbi8oo9dnqcJEkfEAVkvV7pc9DXuAeonpf676Kt3iv4KVyYN5Y-BbxuMQ7gvDwmx0gQnrBT9Z5GsehH0hVM6FW4v-F_gA69XOW" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
             Foundation
            </a>
           </strong>
           bills itself as \xe2\x80\x9cCulture\xe2\x80\x99s Stock Exchange,\xe2\x80\x9d and features a collection of crypto art that users can invest in and trade.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <ul style="margin: 1em 0;">
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuxCAM_Jrl1ggI5HHg0Et_I-LhTdASiMC0Sr--JHuoZMnyjOzxjNUIa8qnOlJBUgvkxTvFBj71UszEKeHYJCfiy_LMALv2QWGuQI5qgrcafYr3BqVckk0ZO80DFzMdn70w3E7g5mHQFozl4mktuXQWXZ2HaEHBN-QzRSBBbYhHefSfD_7VKtX8m7LubNrb5CPm5Kr1cf24YOIVp5wyxmbWy56OHet0CSPwyo_4egi6r7wr1RTU9nUdIVnFhCbldqLRr03vEG6iGVla32v0eC4QtQng3h7xncr9Mp4HqAg_JQAi5Dd4GZ_GYZBCkqbmUssn_gv9AZs8eN4" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
             Zora
            </a>
           </strong>
           is a marketplace to buy, sell, and trade limited-edition goods by buying one of a limited supply of tokens that\xe2\x80\x99s exchangeable for socks, t-shirts, and more.
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;">
           <strong>
            <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMuOhSAM_ZrL0gCK4ILFbOY3DEJVIoKBMhP_fnwsJmnStM3peViDsKR86iMVJLVAHr3TrOeqFd1AnO4cU0IRX8Y5A-zGB425AjnqFLw16FN8EJRyQVYNzsxuVrIzapaKMzHNg-EWOAUh296Rm2c01XmIFjT8QD5TBBL0iniUT_v14d9XYT5zCqGxab8m4jWnnDLGBtaKlsqGNaYECbzyI26fju4Lb0qdChq73SCSdUw4pezjcp231ezwfLuFj1ffa_R4jhDNFMC9nvBN4ZGI5wE6wm8JgAj5Xd5Glex70Qlysbl05RH_if4AuSJyWA" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
             Roll
            </a>
           </strong>
           mints branded tokens, or social money, giving people and communities their own custom tokens like $SARI, $PACKY, $THANKS, $HOLLA, or $RNG.
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Social tokens provide fans a means of not only sharing financial upside with their favorite creatives but also enable tiered, tokenized access based on fan engagement. For example,
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUD1vwyAQ_TVhtAAbYw8MXbp0q7pbZ7g4KBgsONr635ckQ6WTTndPT-_DAuGW8mmOVIjVgnnxzohRTr0aZubM4MSkJubLcs2IO_hgKFdkR12Dt0A-xSeDc6nYzWjQs3MjWnCrAq61nuW1R95fZQ_aNl7TWaA6j9GiwW_MZ4rIgrkRHeXSv13kexv68USYO5v2dm0Q4Pf8_Ppg3kguuRBiFr3que5EByVolFUe8X4Z-L7JrtS1ENj7g82yiYnWlH3cGny_wY7hCbQES9t7jZ7OBSOsAd0rHL3qeHql80AT8acEfDh6PR-JJz2OalCsqbnUion_Qn_xanXC" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Richard Kim
         </a>
         \xe2\x80\x99s
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkd1qxCAQhZ8m3iWoifm58KJQ9jWCxtlENmrQsdu8fd1soRQU8RvGczyzKIQ1xFMeISHJCeJsjWQ9H1vRTcTIzrBRjMSm-R4BnLK7xJiBHFnvdlFog786KOWCbBKo6KigIEam73wCPXUwtYNoqRm4oZq8dGaVjQW_gIQviGfwQHa5IR6paj8qfitrVbv6PiM-mpR1QrU8miW4UjjKvsfgah9ws36tMdQpOHhfnha3Ovq1am-xaj8Z9aWnz-jmRblD2dUX-rLwSx0Ym11hT9C_KIUcFygIy2MIkVjJKaeMsYm15R9DwxqV9gF45od_VB11K__nkkRZzOkQi6NSfmzKwX4VSmhzOV32Fs8ZvNI7mHee-J7AFQ-eB0gPz7TD5eCCr5DHoe9FJ0hRM6HMwv8J_QAyZp3e" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          Random Number Generator
         </a>
         is a Discord server for founders and investors in the gaming community in which status is determined by the amount of $RNG users hold. Users earn $RNG (minted on Roll) by signing up early, doing cool things for the community, creating, and winning competitions. Members can use the $RNG they earn for both exclusive access and for financial gain, as Kim plans to create fiat liquidity for $RNG holders.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Social tokens allow creators to own, control and coordinate the value that they create across platforms, like a digitally native rewards program with upside for both creators and fans.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         But as much as crypto fans want to believe they\xe2\x80\x99ve created something startling and revolutionary, in reality, the experience feels: unfamiliar (payments happen off-platform), overwhelming (you end up in a confusing maze of wallets - jumping from Coinbase to Metamask to Uniswap, often unclear what you own), and pyramid scheme-y.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         In an
         <a href="https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVkMFuxCAMRL9muW0UICT0wKGX_kZkiDeLQiAC0zZ_X3ZXalXJvvjJM5pxQLimfJojFWK1YJ79YvgotFTDG1vMsHCtNPNlvmXEHXwwlCuyo9rgHZBP8fnR90Kxu3GDGxBGJ4XVVnKpnbSg5Q20nSbFOXv4zFAXj9GhwU_MZ4rIgrkTHeUi3y_io80KAb7PTFtXqi0Ebutc2hs42ma8BXQP63JN8drAXqOnk3kjetFzzt-4VLKfOt5BCROKKo64XYZ-X8U_QZZNTGRT9nFteLvDjuEJWr75V3jGCDbg8opOr7KeSeg80ET8KgGJML-Ojz70NI5qUKy5LanVFv-MfgCy54D0" style="color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">
          excellent post
         </a>
         , Kim reflects on the challenges of token-based communities:
        </p>
        <blockquote style="border-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;">
         <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;">
          <em>
           Whether they acknowledge it or not, tokenized communities are so focused on token price that they lose sight of why they were created to begin with--the shared values and interests, the intrinsic motivators, the glue that is left when all other bindings are stripped away.
          </em>
         </p>
        </blockquote>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         This is common with new technologies -- the first iterations focus too much on the technology itself instead of the user experience the technology facilitates.
        </p>
        <p style="color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">
         Social tokens represent one step in a fundraising progression -- from traditional cap tables and ESOPs towards more programmable, easily exchangeable money that fits into the flow of a well thought out user experience.
        </p>
